description:
No original box or spare laces
Not sure what year these are actually from; sometime in the 2000's.
These have the all-star tongue tag, so you know they're from a very brief period of time. (very rare for the hi's)
They also have the old style of license plate at the rear (admittedly kind of faded)
I don't believe this is a pair of the lites, but the midsole is thinner than newer pairs for some reason.
No idea if this was a collaboration or a one-off print design.
Some textured accents around the canvas, assorted newsprint graphics throughout.
I can't even recall what they say, but it looks cool at least.
Some discoloration from age/wear.
They were washed a couple years ago, and I haven't worn them since.
Still some discoloration and rough edges, but they're clean.
I think that I put some sole-whitener on the midsoles at some point - so traces of that can be found around both shoes. I don't believe any got on the canvas but the outer-soles have some residue. Not a big deal -- it's cleanable.
Laces are a bit dirty as well, size tags inside the tongues are quite faded.
No holes, stains, loose threads, odors, etc.
